
/*
 * The Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes from one collection to another. It retrieves all nodes under the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] and appends them to the [payload] node's children collection. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified destination node.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves all nodes under the [.arguments] node.
 */
add:x:+/*/payload
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
